  "description": "Service-level overview for the CouchDB instance used by the homelab.\n\nThe dashboard combines three views:\n- Health: exporter scrape status, public HTTPS endpoint availability and HTTP 5xx error share.\n- Traffic: request volume and breakdown by HTTP status code.\n- Internals: Erlang VM memory usage and internal resource counters such as open databases and OS file descriptors.\n\nUse this dashboard to quickly answer:\n- Is CouchDB reachable both from the monitoring stack and from the public HTTP path?\n- How much traffic is the node handling and how clean are the responses?\n- Are there signs of internal resource pressure that could explain latency or error spikes?\n\nAlerting rules for CouchDB are defined in `couchdb.rules.yml` and reuse the same metrics surfaced here.",
  "editable": true,
  "fiscalYearStartMonth": 0,
  "graphTooltip": 0,
  "id": 21,
